<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-07-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-07-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="918" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d918">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName></hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-07-23"><hi rend="italic">July 23,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 762.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received and communicated to the
                            Secretary of the Navy your telegram of the 21st instant, which
                            deciphered reads as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>British Government has made inquiry and is convinced there is no
                                    truth in report of Spanish privateer at Vancouver.</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>Respectfully, yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">J. B. Moore</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>